Rotary club district 9141 has trained female students in Yenagoa,  Bayelsa State on menstrual hygiene, and the production of sanitary pads. Speaking during the training, Assistant Governor for Rotary Club zone 13 and Coordinator Rotary district 9141, Rotarian Obioma Obikeze, said the ‘pad a girl project’ in Bayelsa was very important for awareness purposes. Man, 60, hangs self in Kano Reps concurs, extend 2021 budget implementation to May 31 According to him: “Those we train here today can make a sanitary pad for themselves, it will be hygienically adaptable to their size and serve a purpose in which it was created for. 